   {:e #blake3 "bb596a426e029e1af6ba0f0e55ced35d84d14223e1a810f97a4940a645ddef5a" :a :task/description :v "UNIT TESTS: (1) test_fingerprint_uses_known_hashes: Create tempdir store with 5 txns via DiskLayout::init + write_tx. Open LiveStore (knows 5). Write 2 more .edn files directly to disk (simulating external process). Call live.flush(). Read meta.json — verify tx_hashes array has exactly 5 entries, not 7. Verify fingerprint computed from those 5. (2) test_stale_flush_triggers_rebuild: After test 1, open a NEW LiveStore. list_tx_hashes returns 7. txn_fingerprint(7) ≠ meta.txn_fingerprint(5). read_slim_cache returns None (cache miss). Store rebuilt from all 7 .edn files. Verify store.len() includes datoms from all 7. (3) test_fresh_flush_is_cache_hit: Create store, open LiveStore, write 3 txns through LiveStore, flush. Reopen. Verify cache HIT (fingerprint matches). Verify store.len() correct. PROPTEST: (4) proptest_subset_fingerprint_differs: Generate n random hashes (5..20). Take subset of size k<n. Verify txn_fingerprint(subset) ≠ txn_fingerprint(full). Run 1000 iterations. FAILURE DIAGNOSTIC: On test failure, print: (a) meta.json tx_hashes array, (b) list_tx_hashes() result, (c) both fingerprints, (d) diff of hash sets. E2E SCRIPT: (5) scripts/e2e_fingerprint.sh: Start braid in tempdir. Run braid observe 'X'. In background, write a raw .edn file to txns/ (simulating concurrent agent). Run braid observe 'Y'. Run braid status. Verify BOTH X and Y appear. If Y missing → fingerprint bug still present." :op :assert}
